# Documentation Navigation Rules

When editing `README.md` or files under `docs/`, preserve this canonical tutorial order:

`INTRO -> BACKPRESSURE -> TECH_STACK -> CLAUDE_SETUP -> BEADS_SETUP -> first-project -> AGENT_LOOP -> FINAL`

## README Requirements

- Keep an ordered reference table for the first six tutorial docs.
- Keep `AGENT_LOOP` and `FINAL` presented as end-of-tutorial reading.
- Do not duplicate long framework/resource prose in `README.md`; link to dedicated docs pages instead.

## Footer Link Rules for docs/*

- Prefer one `_Next:` link for forward movement.
- Use `_See also:` only for related references that do not break the main sequence.
- Keep `[← Back to README](../README.md)` at the bottom.

## Reference Placement

- Put practical setup/framework comparisons in dedicated docs pages.
- Put external reading lists in dedicated reference/next-step docs pages.
- Avoid repeating the same external links in multiple docs unless there is a clear reason.
